One in every four mobile users who encountered malware in 2017, were attacked by malicious programs that used adult content to lure them into installing it on their devices.The statistic was revealed by cybersecurity company Kaspersky Lab, which said that over 1.2 million people had fallen victim to attacks. This followed research into cyberthreats facing users of adult websites and apps.Roman Unuchek, security expert at Kaspersky, said that although the company could not pinpoint that porn-themed mobile applications are technically very different to those that do not use porn in their activities, there are a few specifics when it comes to attacks with porn-powered malicious applications. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssqX8Ar85Sz0DNxmMskxxwtQTj7ySmL4k2155ODZi2ZenEG4j8GwTcAgmeTxEMZlzZboekTxx_c445Bt0GnJOIyTsfg8uUaICGHPkLJZeZX_1B9QNRMdBNGwCd6V42h9VV5ztBdAcNe6xpvN_dzkYKA3VLWVjTka5YNbh869BTE_4iFull4qbyW4CP69copa_2aXY4T18eZNxL9Blf945wraMMHkPrpH1fnhvSR5SAEokZrGW4-bUz2VKgYgrL-_Mn-ptS7EKrRSYJVXaypk6Xdosn9EmI\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzCQPGWAwcdWDEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
